    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nIf I opened a `:checkhealth` window (with `vim.g.health = { style = 'float' }`), and call a command which changes the focused buffer (such as `:spl ...` or `:tabe ...`), the `checkhealth` window will not be closed.\n\nHere's a `minimal.lua` repro file:\n\n```lua\nvim.g.health = { style = 'float' }\n```\n\nOne could argue this is wanted when the health buffers are non-floating (as they are a buffer window in their own right), but when it's a floating window I expect it to close when the `BufLeave` event fires.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nnvim --clean -u minimal.lua\n:checkhealth\n:spl foo.lua\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe `:checkhealth` window should be closed when the \"focus\" changes.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.12, nightly\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nLinux, Fedora 43\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nwezterm\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from source",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Ref https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/39312#issuecomment-4296517805\n\n> thought about it carefully, and I don’t think it’s worth opening a PR just to fix these two issues. g:style is inherently a temporary thing. :float modifier https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/31902 and previewpopup https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/26799 should probably be moved forward instead. I’ll revisit https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/26799 these days..",
