        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "While `g:health` is a temporary \"fix\" as you put it, it's handy to configure the aspect of `:checkhealth` system-wide. It can be complementary to `:float` (which I did not know about).\n\nCompare it to `'winborder'`: yes, you can specify `{..., border = 'single', ...}` in every call which opens a new window, but it's much easier to specify it once and for all, with the option to override it on a single call.",
